data.title: EveryPolitician: Germany
data.meta_description: Data about every national legislature in the world, freely available for you to use.
data.text:
Ruby programmer? Its easy to use this data in your own app! Use the gem like this:

require 'everypolitician' country = Everypolitician::Index.new.country('Germany') house = country.legislature('Bundestag') house.popolo.terms.find_by(id: 'term/3').memberships.each do |membership| puts "#{membership.person.name} (#{membership.party.name}): #{membership.person.gender}" end
